The new model refines the `inner_loop_model` by splitting the alternation penalty into two weights (under-alternating vs over-alternating). This allows the model to heavily penalize clustered sequences (under-alternating) while tolerating or rewarding highly alternating sequences, satisfying the significant empirical discrepancy where people still prefer over-alternating sequences more often than the symmetric model expects.

